  "texts": [
    "Ganesan et al. [100] and Bahurudeen et al.",
    "[101] found that incorporating SCBA up to a 20% replacement level reduces workability by 5-15% and extends setting time by 5-10%.",
    "In line with these findings, Cordeiro et al. [102] reported a slight decrease in workability and air content, attributed to the fine particles of SCBA filling in the gaps within the mix.",
    "Similarly, Murugesan et al. and Singh et al.",
    "[103] observed small reductions in slump flow and slight increases in setting time at lower SCBA replacement levels of 5-15%."
  ],
